                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/hist-221" class="program-course-title">
              HIST 221 United States since 1865 (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-27416" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: History and Classical Studies (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      History              : Examines the defining moments and movements in the U.S. since Reconstruction, including populism, progressivism, the World Wars, the New Deal, the Cold War, the sixties and its consequences. Emphasis on the political, social and ideological transformations that ensued.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Shanon Fitzpatrick (Winter)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Fall</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
