                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/econ-426" class="program-course-title">
              ECON 426 Labour Economics (3 credits)              *            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-22420" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Economics (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Economics (Arts)              : The determinants of labour supply, demand and the structure of earnings are considered. The economic effects of government policies, such as minimum wage laws, unemployment insurance, welfare and training programs and subsidies to higher education are analyzed. A rigorous theoretical and "hands on'' empirical approach is emphasized.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:              There are no professors associated with this course for the 2014-2015 academic year.          </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Prerequisite: ECON 230D1/D2 or ECON 250D1/D2 or ECON 306D1/D2.</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
